Figure 5.5.7.1-1 illustrates the inter-frequency RSTD measurement indication, which is a crucial aspect of telecommunication systems. The figure depicts the relationship between different frequency bands and the resulting Root-Mean-Square Delay Tolerance (RSTD) values. This information is essential for optimizing signal processing and ensuring reliable communication between devices. The figure shows how RSTD varies with frequency, highlighting the impact of signal propagation and absorption on the overall system performance. The visual representation of this complex concept makes it easier to understand and apply in practical scenarios.
Figure 5.5.7.1-1: Inter-frequency RSTD measurement indication
